MysticCube
--------------------------------------

  drag'n'drop picture viewer on a cube
  
  written by captain bifat / TEK neoscientists


introduction
--------------------------------------

  welcome to another workbench toy.

  MystiCube opens a scalable window on the default pubscreen
  with a rotating, texture-mapped cube. you can drag'n'drop
  pictures on the cube's faces in order to display them.

  MystiCube works on all kinds of screen modes (including hi- and
  truecolor).

  press 't' for a frames-per-second counter.
  press 'r' to obtain an RGB cube.
  press 'i' to turn faces inside out.
  press '+' and '-' to zoom in/out.


demonstrated features
--------------------------------------

  MystiCube is a quick hack to demonstrate some features of
  guigfx.library.

  - dynamic palette creation with a set of different pictures
  - screen-pen management
  - datatype loading
  - texture-mapping
  

